    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix ASN.1 encoding in PDU session release response transfer\n\n### Summary\nThe NGAP PDU session release response function was incorrectly copying raw transfer data instead of properly encoding it as an ASN.1 structure. This caused malformed NGAP messages to be sent to the AMF during PDU session release procedures.\n\nThe issue was in `ngap_gNB_pdusession_release_resp()` where `allocCopy()` was used to directly copy the transfer data without ASN.1 encoding, unlike the setup and modify response functions which properly encode their transfer structures.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NGAP/ngap_gNB_nas_procedures.c`: Replaced direct memory copy with proper ASN.1 encoding of PDUSessionResourceReleaseResponseTransfer structure following the same pattern as other response functions.\n\nUnder high PDU session release load, this would cause AMF to reject the release responses due to malformed transfer IEs, leading to stuck PDU sessions and memory leaks in the gNB.\n"
}